<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1910-01-17T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1910-01-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="79" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d79">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 4737/35.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Ambassador <persName type="to">Dudley</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-01-17"><hi rend="italic">January 17,
                                1910</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>The Government and people of the United States sincerely deplore the loss
                            Brazil suffers in the death of the ambassador, who in his work among us
                            has won the esteem and good will of all.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Knox.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>